author: rpenoyer
msg: Create Works!. To use this implementation however, the method GetConnection
in the SQLEntryImpl class must be set to a database schema with the following tables:
MAIN - ID NUMBER, PARENT, NUMBER, DNPATH VARCHAR, ENTRY VARCHAR,
TIMESTAMP DATE, CREATOR_NAME VARCHAR, CHANGE_TIMESTAMP DATE,
ATTRIBUTES - NAME VARCHAR, MAINID NUMBER, RDN VARCHAR, VALUE VARCHAR
Also, you must add the jdbc drive jar file for your target database to ldap-server/lib. Then modify
the build.xml to include the JDBC driver jar in the sar target build.
Binary attributes do not work yet.
